column10: Were there any vulnerability markers on the customers account?
column11: Q1-Did the advisor process Personal Data in accordance with the Data protection Act?
column12: Q1 - Failure Reasons
column13: Q2 - Did the advisor confirm the customer's or authorised 3rd party's contact telephone number, email, and up to date home address and update date the system accordingly if required?
column15: Q3 - Did the advisor understand the customer's past financial situation including the reason they have failed or may fail to pay Three?
column17: Q4 -  Did the advisor understand the customer's present financial situation?
column18: Q4 - Failure Reasons
column19: Q5 - Did the advisor understand the customer's future financial situation?
column21: Q6 - Did the advisor correctly identify & explore new vulnerability needs?
column23: Q7 - Did the advisor correctly acknowledge & explore existing vulnerability needs?
column25: Q8 - Where applicable did the advisor address any new accessibility needs during their interaction?
column27: Q9 - Where applicable did the advisor address any existing accessibility needs during their interaction?
column28: Q9 - Failure Reasons
column29: Q10 - Did the advisor gain full explicit consent to note the customer's new vulnerability and/or accessibility need?
column30: Q10 - Failure Reasons
column31: Q11 - Did the advisor update the system to accurately reflect the customer's vulnerability and/or accessibility needs?
column33: Q12 - Did the advisor establish a suitable solution that supported the customer's needs taking into account their information from the conversation ?
column34: Q12 - Failure Reasons
column35: Q13 - Did the advisor read any mandatory statements/tell them in a manner that was easy for the customer to understand?
column37: Q14 - Did we clearly advise the customer of any next steps required by them and did they explain potential consequeses for adherance/non adherance to any outcome?
column39: Q15 - Was the Income and Expenditure Tool completed correctly?
column41: Q16 - Has the advisor taken the correct system action
column43: Q17 - System updates - When payment has been taken on call/chat
column44: Q17 - Failure Reasons
column45: Q18 - Did the advisor leave adequate notes regarding the interaction?
column47: Q19-If an expression of dissatisfaction was evident, was it addressed by the agent , and correct process followed
column49: Q20-Was any new suspicious activity evident during the call/ interactions you’re scoring (i.e. not instances already identified/ flagged that pre-date the call/ interactions you’re scoring)? (non-scoring)
column50: Q20.1-If yes: did the advisor correctly identify the activity as suspicious?
column51: Q21-If applicable, did the advisor then follow the relevant process correctly and avoid “tipping off” the customer?
column52: Q22 - During the interaction did the advisor act within our expected conduct realms:
column55: Q23-CD Focus: Did the advisor and/or Three deal with the customer in an honest, fair, and open manner and by acting how our customers would reasonably expect us to?
column57: Q24-CD Focus: Did the advisor and/or Three take all reasonable steps to prevent foreseeable or actual customer harm?
column59: Q25-CD Focus: Did the advisor and/or Three provide adequate levels of support, enabling customers to make timely and informed decisions in their best interests?
